records.addlTxt:
Defendant Luke R Steidl in court with attorney Joel Winnig.  Melissa Zilavy appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.   Counts #2 and #3 are dismissed and read into count #1.   The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

3 MONTHS JAIL;

TERM OF PROBATION:  1 YEAR;

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*No Use or Possession of controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain full time employment and/or combination of schooling 
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.
*Perform 50 Hours of Community Service.

FINE: $363.25 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $200.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

CONDITION TIME: 30 DAYS, STAYED; to be used at agent's discretion.  Agent to determine with or without non working hours.  

EXPUNGEMENT: Request for expungement is NOT granted by the Court.
